{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876868904,"sessionID":"ses_2857dc469ffeojq7kAd1VhpFg5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a828816001g9XvDvQOSgfVWP","messageID":"msg_d7a8273f2001EOVxx55Aghzsom","sessionID":"ses_2857dc469ffeojq7kAd1VhpFg5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5d786549ec8f43b191bdd8f26bddb711","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The CodeInterpreterClient is a Python SDK that provides a high-level interface for interacting with the CodeInterpreter service. It abstracts the underlying HTTP communication and provides a clean, type-safe API for managing code execution sessions.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: 1. **CodeInterpreterClient**: Main client class for interacting with the CodeInterpreter service\n12: 2. **Session Manager**: Manages CodeInterpreter session lifecycle\n13: 3. **Execution Manager**: Handles code execution requests\n14: 4. **Result Processor**: Processes and validates execution results\n15: \n16: ### Key Features\n17: \n18: - Session creation, retrieval, and termination\n19: - Code execution with synchronous and asynchronous modes\n20: - Result streaming and batch retrieval\n21: - Error handling and retry logic\n22: - Type-safe request/response models\n23: \n24: ## API Design\n25: \n26: ### Client Initialization\n27: \n28: ```python\n29: from agentcube.sdk import CodeInterpreterClient\n30: \n31: client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n32:     base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n33:     api_key=\"your-api-key\"\n34: )\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ### Session Management\n38: \n39: ```python\n40: # Create session\n41: session = client.create_session(\n42:     workspace_id=\"workspace-123\",\n43:     timeout=300\n44: )\n45: \n46: # Get session\n47: session = client.get_session(session_id=\"session-123\")\n48: \n49: # List sessions\n50: sessions = client.list_sessions(workspace_id=\"workspace-123\")\n51: \n52: # Delete session\n53: client.delete_session(session_id=\"session-123\")\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ### Code Execution\n57: \n58: ```python\n59: # Execute code synchronously\n60: result = client.execute_code(\n61:     session_id=\"session-123\",\n62:     code=\"print('Hello, World!')\"\n63: )\n64: \n65: # Execute code asynchronously\n66: job = client.execute_code_async(\n67:     session_id=\"session-123\",\n68:     code=\"x = 1 + 1\"\n69: )\n70: \n71: # Get execution result\n72: result = client.get_execution_result(job_id=\"job-123\")\n73: ```\n74: \n75: ## Data Models\n76: \n77: ### Session\n78: \n79: ```python\n80: class Session(BaseModel):\n81:     session_id: str\n82:     workspace_id: str\n83:     status: SessionStatus\n84:     created_at: datetime\n85:     updated_at: datetime\n86:     timeout: int\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ### ExecutionResult\n90: \n91: ```python\n92: class ExecutionResult(BaseModel):\n93:     job_id: str\n94:     session_id: str\n95:     status: ExecutionStatus\n96:     output: str\n97:     error: Optional[str]\n98:     execution_time: float\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ## Error Handling\n102: \n103: - Custom exception types for different error scenarios\n104: - Automatic retry logic for transient errors\n105: - Detailed error messages with context\n106: \n107: ## Testing Strategy\n108: \n109: - Unit tests for client methods\n110: - Integration tests with mock CodeInterpreter service\n111: - End-to-end tests with real service (when available)\n112: \n113: ## Dependencies\n114: \n115: - httpx ^0.24.0 (HTTP client)\n116: - pydantic ^2.0.0 (data validation)\n117: - typing-extensions ^4.0.0 (type hints)\n118: \n119: ## Future Enhancements\n120: \n121: - WebSocket support for streaming output\n122: - Session persistence and recovery\n123: - Advanced debugging features\n124: - Custom execution environment configuration\n\n(End of file - total 124 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThe CodeInterpreterClient is a Python SDK that provides a high-level interface for interacting with the CodeInterpreter service. It abstracts the underlying HTTP communication and provides a clean, type-safe API for managing code execution sessions.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n1. **CodeInterpreterClient**: Main client class for interacting with the CodeInterpreter service\n2. **Session Manager**: Manages CodeInterpreter session lifecycle\n3. **Execution Manager**: Handles code execution requests\n4. **Result Processor**: Processes and validates execution results\n\n### Key Features\n\n- Session creation, retrieval, and termination\n- Code execution with synchronous and asynchronous modes\n- Result streaming and batch retrieval","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/design.md","time":{"start":1775876868837,"end":1775876868901}}}}
